(3) Where a claim in writing is made by any person that is lawfully entitled to the property seized under this Act that the property is not liable to forfeiture under this Act the Commissioner may order release of the property to the claimant if satisfied that there is no dispute as to ownership of the property and that it is not liable for forfeiture.
